cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.SE 

This paper is about an architecture for artificial intelligence, which is a broad topic that could fit into several sub-categories. However, given the focus on neural networks and problem solving methods for statistical tasks, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely given the emphasis on neural networks. cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are less likely but still possible given the discussion of software architecture and modular design.
